org.orgName: The District Court of the United States, Western District of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: In the United States District Court
For the Western District of Washington
In the Matter of the Petition of Sakutaro Kuwahara for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
Filed in the United States District Court
In the Matter of the Petition of Sakutaro Kuwahara for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.

In this cause the order to show cause why a Writ of Habeas Corpus should not issue,heretofore granted herein on the 21st day of January, 1920, having come on for hearing and argument on the 2nd day of February, 1920, and the court having on that day heard the argument,took the matter under advisement, and on the 4th day of February, 1920, filed and opinion and decision herein granting and allowing the Writ of Habeas Corpus, and on the 5th day of February, 1920, made and entered an order herein granting and allowing a Writ of Habeas Corpus, and said Writ of Habeas Corpus having been issued and return thereon having been made by Henry M.White, United States Commissioner of Immigration at the Port of Seattle, setting out the cause of the detention of Hisayo Kuwahara as set out in his return herein to the order to show cause, basing said detention upon the same record and proceedings; and the said Henry M.White, United States Commissioner of Immigration at the Port of Seattle, having produced in open court the body of said Hisayo Kuwahara, it is by the court

ORDER, CONSIDERED and ADJUDGED, and the court does hereby ORDER, CONSIDER and ADJUDGE, that the said Hisayo Kuwahara be, and she is hereby discharged, freed and enlarged from said detention, and that she go hence without day.
Done in Open Court this 7th day of February, 1920.
